\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
Proof
\emph default
.
 We know that 
\begin_inset Formula $\gcd(a,n)=sa+tn$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $s,t\in\Z$
\end_inset

, so if 
\begin_inset Formula $\gcd(a,n)=1$
\end_inset

, then we have 
\begin_inset Formula $sa+tn=1$
\end_inset

.
 But we're working in 
\begin_inset Formula $\Z_{n}$
\end_inset

, so 
\begin_inset Formula $tn\cong0$
\end_inset

, so we really have 
\begin_inset Formula $sa=1$
\end_inset

.
 But then 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 is a unit, which is 
\emph on
quod erat demonstrandum
\emph default
.
